  "bio_raw": "A O M Shamsuddoha joined the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh, as a Lecturer in the Department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering in May 2023. Before that, he worked as a full-time Lecturer at The Internation University of Scholars, as an adjunct Lecturer at Ahsanullah University of Science and Technology, and as a contractual Lecturer at Daffodil International University. He is currently pursuing his MSc. in EEE specializing in VLSI/Electronics from Ahsanullah University of Science and Technology. He has completed his BSc. in EEE from Ahsanullah University of Science and Technology.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Low Power VLSI Circuit Design, Semiconductor Characterization, Novel Transistor Architecture"
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMSc. in EEE\n, Ahsanullah University of Science and Technology (Ongoing)\nBSc. in EEE\n, Ahsanullah University of Science and Technology"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Conference Proceedings\nS. Chakraborty, S. Zahir, N. T. Orchi, M. F. Bin Hafiz,\nA. O. M. Shamsuddoha\nand S. M. Dipto, \"Violence Detection: A Multi-Model Approach Towards Automated Video Surveillance and Public Safety,\"\n2024 International Conference on Advances in Computing, Communication, Electrical, and Smart Systems (iCACCESS)\n, Dhaka, Bangladesh, 2024, pp. 1-6, doi: 10.1109/iCACCESS61735.2024.10499466.\nA. O. M. Shamsuddoha\n, M. K. Islam, “A Review Paper on Recent Applications of Auger Electron Spectroscopy (AES) Technology in Semiconductor Industry for Semiconductor Characterization,” International Conference on Electronics and Informatics 2022, Bangladesh Electronics and Informatics Society, 27 January 2023.\nS. J. Hamim, M. K. Islam,\nA. O. M. Shamsuddoha\n, S. Dhar and A. K. M. Baki, \"Performance evaluation of 2×2 and massive 8×8 MIMO at 28 GHz and 60 GHz for Dhaka City,\" 2022 IEEE 7th International Conference for Convergence in Technology (I2CT), 2022, pp. 1-5, doi: 10.1109/I2CT54291.2022.9825246.\nA. O. M. Shamsuddoha\n, M. K. Islam and S. N. Biswas, \"Design and Performance Analysis of SRAM Circuit Using Adiabatic Logic with FinFET,\" 2021 International Conference on Electronics, Communications and Information Technology (ICECIT), Bangladesh, 2021, pp. 1-4, doi: 10.1109/ICECIT54077.2021.9641167.",
    "Training/Workshop Attended\nTraining on Teaching for Active Learning | Foundation for Learning, Teaching, and Research | September 14-16, 2023\nTraining on Outcome-Based Curriculum and Accreditation Standards and Criteria | University of Scholars | April 16-18, 2022\nVirtual BCI & Neurotechnology Spring School | g.tec medical engineering GmbH, Austria | April 12-21, 2021.\nOnline Workshop on Quantum Systems Engineering for Scientists | IEEE Quantum | February 11, 2021"
